averages. In the aggregate, July 2024 day-ahead and real-time LMPs were approximately 9% higher during July 2024 than during July 2023. Average natural gas prices were 33% below the prior year’s average prices, while residual fuel prices were up 9% over a year ago.Overall, the average of the real-time LMPs at the Hub and in the Load Zones ranged between 7.7% lower than its day-ahead counterpart in the Southeastern Massachusetts (SEMA) Load Zone to 6.9% lower than its day-ahead counterpart in the Vermont (VT) Load Zone. In the DayAhead Market, Load Zone average LMPs ranged between 2.2% lower than the Hub average LMPs in the Connecticut (CT) Load Zone to 1.6% higher than the Hub in the NortheasternMassachusetts (NEMA) Load Zone. In the Real-Time Market, Load Zone average LMPs ranged between 1.5% lower than the Hub average LMPs in the CT Load Zone to 1.5% higher than the Hub in the NEMA Load Zone. Price differentials between on-peak and off-peak hours at the Hub and in the Load Zones ranged between 44% and 83% in both the Day-Ahead and Real-Time Markets.The New England Control Area was a net importer of electricity in the Real-Time Market during July. In the Day-Ahead Energy Market, there were approximately 564,000 MWh of total exports and 1,798,000 MWh of imports, yielding a net import of approximately 1,234,000 MWh. In the Real-Time Energy Market, there were approximately 901,000 MWh of total exports and 2,076,000 MWh of imports, yielding a net import of approximately 1,175,000 MWh. This was about 16,000 MWh higher than a year ago. The Monthly, or Prompt Month FTR Auction (July 2024) had 21 participants and the awarded value of FTRs in the auction totaled $750K. This represented an increase of $416K over the previous month, and a decrease of about $587K from the prior year’s monthly FTR auction. The allocation of FTR Auction Revenue for July 2024 resulted in $1.97 million awarded to eligible entities, with $132K allocated to Incremental Auction Revenue Rights (IARR).